READ CAPTION:

1. Over line only the Cupid’s bow and bottom center – not the corners.
	2.	Clean edges with concealer after applying lipstick.
	3.	Set lipstick with tissue + translucent powder for longer wear.
	4.	Use two lip liners – darker on the outer edges, lighter in the center.
	5.	Highlight the Cupid’s bow and center of the lower lip.
	6.	Use blush as a lip tint – top with clear gloss.
	7.	Contour under the lower lip to create a fuller-looking pout.
	8.	Apply lip balm before makeup, then wipe it off before lip liner for smooth application.
	9.	Dab a little foundation over lips before lipstick for truer color payoff.
	10.	Use matte lipstick as a lip liner if you don’t have one handy.
“Royalty in every detail, especially the liner 👑💖”
